      <sectiondef kind="func">
      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__uartns550_1ga4b3eb97421a6a66e7029e9afafd8a74b" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int XUartNs550_SetDataFormat</definition>
        <argsstring>(XUartNs550 *InstancePtr, XUartNs550Format *FormatPtr)</argsstring>
        <name>XUartNs550_SetDataFormat</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_x_uart_ns550" kindref="compound">XUartNs550</ref> *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_x_uart_ns550_format" kindref="compound">XUartNs550Format</ref> *</type>
          <declname>Format</declname>
          <defname>FormatPtr</defname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Sets the data format for the specified UART. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The data format includes the baud rate, number of data bits, number of stop bits, and parity. It is the caller&apos;s responsibility to ensure that the UART is not sending or receiving data when this function is called.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_uart_ns550" kindref="compound">XUartNs550</ref> instance . </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>FormatPtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to a format structure containing the data format to be set.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><verbatim>    - XST_SUCCESS if the data format was successfully set.
    - XST_UART_BAUD_ERROR indicates the baud rate could not be set
    because of the amount of error with the baud rate and the input
    clock frequency.
    - XST_INVALID_PARAM if one of the parameters was not valid.
</verbatim></para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para></para></simplesect>
The data types in the format type, data bits and parity, are 32 bit fields to prevent a compiler warning that is a bug with the GNU PowerPC compiler. The asserts in this function will cause a warning if these fields are bytes. <linebreak/>
<linebreak/>
 The baud rates tested include: 1200, 2400, 4800, 9600, 19200, 38400, 57600 and 115200. </para>        </detaileddescription>
